Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle, curving. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium, buff-brown; mixed inclusions.
Curator's comments: Petrie drew three such stamps (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.53, 4; 122, 16 and 201.25). Name Sthennidas. From the same die as a piece from Tanis, H. Melaerts, ‘Timbres amphoriques d’Egypte’ Chronique d’Egypte 69 (1994), 347, no.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0467)
